page.title: 18THE BACKWATERS
page.content: At the Backwaters there are a lot of very small sailing boats which people keep for pleasure.There is a track which goes round near the Backwaters and finishes near Saville Street.Round the track are many different plants and flowers.Going round you can see many different sites like the old Foundary and lots of caravans which belong to the caravan sites.There are many old boats that you see walking round,there is the old concrete barges.You will find many sheep fences which you have to climb over.The Backwaters make a lovely walk.
